<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6622894>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Dorsolateral and ventral views of the specimens in life: comparative specimen of Xenophrys maosonensis from Cao Bang Province (IEBR A.4970) (A, B), the holotype of Xenophrys truongsonensis sp. nov. (IEBR A.4940) (C, D) Photos by C.V. Hoang and C.T. Pham" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6622894/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6622896>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Lateral view of the head (A), right food (B), right hand (C), back of thigh (D) and flank (E) of the holotype (IEBR A.4940) of Xenophrys truongsonensis sp. nov.; comparative specimen of X. maosonensis (IEBR A.4970) (F, G, H, I, K). White spots on back of thigh (a), white spots on flank (b). Photos by A.M. Luong" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6622896/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6622898>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitat of Xenophrys truongsonensis sp. nov. in Vietnam:A) forest in Bi Doup-Nui Ba NP, Lam Dong Province; B) forest in Chu Yang Sin NP, Dak Lak Province; C) forest in Phuoc Binh NP, Ninh Thuan Province; and D) forest in Kon Plong, Kon Tum Province. Photos by A.M. Luong and C.T. Pham" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6622898/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6622900>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Map showing the distribution of Xenophrys truongsonensis sp. nov. in Vietnam: 1) Dak Lak Province (type locality), 2) Thua Thien Hue Province, 3) Quang Nam Province, 4) Kon Tum Province, 5) Dak Nong Province, 6) Lam Dong Province, and 7) Ninh Thuan Province." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6622900/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

